		<exercise>
			<title>Statements</title>
			<idx><h>Statements</h></idx>
			<statement>
				<p>
Consider the following two statements:
<ul>
<li>
<m>P = </m> The rent increases.
</li>
<li>
<m>Q = </m> I will renew my lease.
</li>
</ul>
Express the following statements in words.
				</p>
				<p>
<ol>
	<li>
		<p>
		<m>P \vee Q</m>
		</p>		
	</li>
	<li>
		<p>
		<m>(\neg P) \wedge Q</m>
		</p>		
	</li>	
	<li>
		<p>
		<m>(\neg P) \Rightarrow Q</m>
		</p>		
	</li>
	<li>
		<p>
		<m>P \Rightarrow (\neg Q)</m>
		</p>		
	</li>
</ol>
				

